ewick","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Colwick (Nottinghamshire), but in the West Midlands perhaps alternatively from Colewick (lost, in Saint Johns in Bedwardine, Worcestershire) or Colewich (Staffordshire), for which see also   Colledge  . The placenames are formed either with the Old English personal name <i>Cola</i> or with Old English <i>col</i> ‘coal, charcoal’ + Old English <i>wic</i> ‘dairy farm’ (see   Wick  ). The surname <i>Colwick</i> is no longer found in Britain. Compare   Collick  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Collick","meanings":["English:","nickname from Middle English <i>collok</i> ‘tankard, bowl, or pail’.","habitational name from any of several places, including Colhook Common in Petworth (Sussex), Colwick in Nottinghamshire (see   Colwick  ), and perhaps a lost or unidentified place in Somerset or Devon."]},{"name":"Colledge","meanings":["English (Midlands and northern England): habitational name from Colwich in Staffordshire, named from Old English <i>col</i> ‘(char)coal’ + <i>wīc</i> ‘building’. The name has become associated with the familiar word <i>college</i>."]}]},{"name":"Reginald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Norman origin, derived from <i>Reginaldus</i>, a Latinized form of   Reynold   influenced by Latin <i>regina</i> ‘queen’. The full form is now regarded as very formal, and bearers generally shorten it to   Reg   in ordinary usage."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Reginald de Colewick was born in 1175, in Colwick, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William de Colewick, was 25 and his mother, F Colewick, was 20. He married F Colewick in 1198, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died before 2 June 1252."},"et":{"1175–Bef 2 June 1252":"1175–enne 2. juunit 1252","1175–1252